1
00:00:20,625 --> 00:00:22,208
[MALE ANOTHER 1]
You truly think it's possible

2
00:00:22,291 --> 00:00:24,583
to be happily married
to a human woman?

3
00:00:25,708 --> 00:00:28,958
I certainly have no reason
to believe that's true.

4
00:00:29,041 --> 00:00:30,333
[MALE ANOTHER 2]
Well, you are wrong.

5
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:36,625
And I fully intend to prove it
to you, this time.

6
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:37,958
You won't be able to deny

7
00:00:38,041 --> 00:00:40,208
the evidence
of our eternal love.

8
00:02:16,916 --> 00:02:18,750
[gunfire on video game]

9
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,791
[ARATA]
Izumi! You over there?

10
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,333
[IZUMI giggles]
Guess we'll see!

11
00:02:22,416 --> 00:02:24,083
[ARATA groans]

12
00:02:24,166 --> 00:02:26,625
Gotcha!
That's six in a row!

13
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:28,083
[yawns]

14
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:29,791
[ARATA]
It doesn't count.

15
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:32,458
I'm out of practice,
so give me a break.

16
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:35,750
Now that you have a real job,
you've turned into a weakling!

17
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:37,375
Weakling!

18
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:39,458
Shut up. Let's play one more.

19
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:41,666
You're gonna be sorry
you said that!

20
00:02:44,083 --> 00:02:45,833
Thanks for inviting me over.

21
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:47,666
[ARATA]
You have to go in to work today?

22
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,291
Yeah, sadly.

23
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:52,166
Apparently, we're booked solid
with dinner reservations.

24
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:53,583
Must be rough.

25
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:54,875
But that's the family business.

26
00:02:54,958 --> 00:02:56,541
Most days it's a hassle.

27
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:58,541
But it's not like
I've got much choice.

28
00:02:58,625 --> 00:03:01,625
By the way,
the Kagurazaka festival's soon.

29
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:02,625
Wanna go with me?

30
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:04,791
I almost forgot about that.

31
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,291
Maybe.
Won't your family need you?

32
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:10,958
Hmm. No, I finally demanded
that they give me time off!

33
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:13,583
-Is that a yes?
-That's a weekday?

34
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,000
As long as it's before work.

35
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:17,250
Awesome!
And I'll even let you pay!

36
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,625
Wait, how much is it?

37
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:21,166
Oh, my gosh,
I'm totally kidding, you nerd!

38
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:24,208
It's been so long since we've
been to a festival together!

39
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:25,958
I think it'll be a good time.

40
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:27,666
Me too, I'll see you later.

41
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,083
[door closes]

42
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,708
Uh...

43
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,458
That was ridiculous.

44
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:53,583
But I finally managed
to lose him.

45
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:56,750
Your guard dog is persistent.
You should be proud.

46
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,458
[MALE ANOTHER 2]
What do you want?

47
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,375
[COYOTE]
Only to thank you for earlier.

48
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:03,625
There's no need.

49
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:06,458
Wow. So, this is her, huh?

50
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:09,708
Which parts did you end up
using from the latest girl?

51
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:12,333
[MALE ANOTHER 2]
Voice and the right leg.

52
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:13,833
I'm almost done.

53
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:17,083
She has the eye.
It goes in last.

54
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:18,958
[COYOTE]
Hmm.

55
00:04:19,041 --> 00:04:21,041
All she needs now
is the left hand.

56
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:22,125
Perfect.

57
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,375
I have a certain girl in mind

58
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:24,500
who meets your criteria.

59
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:27,291
I'll tell you more
if you're interested?

60
00:04:27,375 --> 00:04:28,333
Are you sure?

61
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:30,000
As far as I can tell.

62
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:33,916
[chuckles] Just consider it
a thank-you gift.

63
00:04:39,125 --> 00:04:40,291
-[ARATA] Good morni--
-[gasps]

64
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:42,583
Oh, sorry!
I didn't mean to scare you!

65
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:45,166
I'll survive this time.
See you later, Arata.

66
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:49,125
[ARATA] Oh, wow. So, you're not
just headed home, I guess?

67
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:52,166
No, not exactly.
Didn't I tell you?

68
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,375
I'm off to Romania.

69
00:04:53,458 --> 00:04:54,916
I'll be there
the next couple weeks.

70
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,500
Romania? I would love
to see that country.

71
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:00,166
-Have fun.
-[SENDA chuckles]

72
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,583
Work is still work
no matter the location.

73
00:05:02,666 --> 00:05:04,041
Anyway, I'm off.

74
00:05:04,125 --> 00:05:05,708
Thanks for holding down
the fort.

75
00:05:05,791 --> 00:05:07,208
Take care!

76
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:08,375
[door closes]

77
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:10,458
So. We've got a lot to do.

78
00:05:10,541 --> 00:05:12,750
-Head out on patrol.
-Right.

79
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:14,833
You remember
what happened at Toyama Park?

80
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:18,541
-With those girls?
-Uh... how could I forget?

81
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:20,416
Well, a report came in saying
one of the girls

82
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,916
who was captured woke up.

83
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,208
Seriously?

84
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:25,708
I need you to help
with her interview.

85
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:27,958
Kyoichi's on his way
there already.

86
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:30,083
Wait, you're not coming?

87
00:05:30,166 --> 00:05:33,375
There's too much analysis to do,
and you guys can handle it.

88
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,666
Visiting hours will be
over soon, so hurry up.

89
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:36,833
Yeah, you got it.

90
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:52,291
Sorry I'm late.
How's it going?

91
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:54,041
Here's the report
the police gave us.

92
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:56,833
Her name is Yuko Shiba.

93
00:05:56,916 --> 00:05:58,750
She's fully conscious
and remembers everything,

94
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,125
so we were able
to find her address

95
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:01,625
and get some information
on her family,

96
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:04,416
but this is our issue
right here.

97
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,666
Born in 1965?

98
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,125
And if that's true,
that would mean

99
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:09,333
she's in her fifties,

100
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,000
but she doesn't look that way,

101
00:06:12,083 --> 00:06:14,500
and she believes
she's still a teenager.

102
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:17,541
Okay.
What's your take on it?

103
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,916
That she was a teenager
when she was kidnapped?

104
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,791
And then somehow didn't age
the entire time?

105
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:26,000
Yes. That's typical
of a supernatural disappearance.

106
00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:29,541
[door opens, closes]

107
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:33,333
♪

108
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:35,208
You're Yuko Shiba, aren't you?

109
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,166
Uh, yes.

110
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,291
I'm Kyoichi Sakaki.

111
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:42,291
I'm with
the Shinjuko Ward Office.

112
00:06:42,375 --> 00:06:43,416
Here you go.

113
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:49,500
♪

114
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:53,791
'Kay.

115
00:06:55,208 --> 00:06:56,625
Would you mind telling me
what you remember

116
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,708
about what happened to you?

117
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:01,000
Sure. Except I,

118
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:03,000
I don't remember
very much at all.

119
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:04,375
That's okay.

120
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:06,000
Another time, then.

121
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:07,375
How are you feeling?

122
00:07:07,458 --> 00:07:09,458
Are you in pain
or especially sore anywhere?

123
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:13,708
No. Not really, to be honest.

124
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:15,458
That's very good to hear.

125
00:07:15,541 --> 00:07:16,708
Huh.

126
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,000
Now, then.

127
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:19,291
Can you tell me
the name of the school

128
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,958
you're going to this year?

129
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,708
I'm going
to Shirakoma Girls' Academy.

130
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:25,083
Oh, you like it?

131
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:28,166
My best friend Izumi
goes there, too.

132
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,833
She's always saying
how good the choir is.

133
00:07:30,916 --> 00:07:32,708
Sounds like they go
to Nationals a lot.

134
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:37,125
It's true. That's the reason
I wanted to go there.

135
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:38,500
I'm a singer in the choir.

136
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,875
Cool.

137
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:42,166
We were supposed to go
to Nationals this year,

138
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,791
but then that
whole thing happened.

139
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,541
It messed everything up.

140
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,333
What "thing" happened?

141
00:07:50,375 --> 00:07:52,291
I don't know exactly.

142
00:07:52,375 --> 00:07:55,416
I remember it was
after practice ended.

143
00:07:57,666 --> 00:08:00,083
Suddenly, everything
went black.

144
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:03,208
It stayed dark
for a long time after that.

145
00:08:03,291 --> 00:08:05,791
[ARATA] A long time?
No light at all?

146
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:07,375
[SHIBA]
No.

147
00:08:07,458 --> 00:08:08,708
But it's weird,

148
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:11,041
I can still remember
looking down at my hands

149
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,500
and seeing them clearly.

150
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:18,333
And the blackness,
it was like ash or something.

151
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:21,541
It felt like fine, black sand
falling from the sky.

152
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:23,958
[KYOICHI]
Black sand, huh?

153
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,916
Thank you.
Anything else?

154
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,250
Mmm?

155
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:34,791
Actually, yeah.

156
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:36,750
There was a lot of pressure
on my throat.

157
00:08:37,916 --> 00:08:39,708
Like someone was holding
a knife to it.

158
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:41,208
[ARATA]
To your throat?

159
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,416
Does it hurt or feel sore
from that now?

160
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,708
Well, no, but, um,

161
00:08:45,791 --> 00:08:47,791
I got chills thinking
about it just now.

162
00:08:47,875 --> 00:08:50,291
Well, your voice
sounds normal, at least.

163
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:51,458
Maybe a little husky.

164
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:53,083
[gasps]

165
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:54,375
Husky how?

166
00:08:54,458 --> 00:08:56,125
No one's ever said that before.

167
00:08:57,125 --> 00:08:59,791
Let's see.
Can you try singing a high note?

168
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:02,375
The way you would
if you were in choir.

169
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:04,458
Maybe. Give me a sec.

170
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:06,666
[inhales sharply]

171
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,625
Uh... uh...

172
00:09:11,208 --> 00:09:13,833
Oh, no! It's gone!
I can't sing!

173
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:15,125
But why?

174
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,333
[THEO on phone] Got it.
She used to be able to sing

175
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,666
and now, after the incident,
she can't?

176
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,791
We assume it's
from the incident.

177
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:25,875
She can still talk.
It's the singing specifically.

178
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:29,000
She's lost all function
in her higher vocal range.

179
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,583
[THEO] So just
her singing voice was stolen.

180
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:34,250
That's so odd. Is that all?

181
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:35,500
Why do you sound so tense?

182
00:09:35,583 --> 00:09:37,541
[THEO]
I just got a call.

183
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:39,833
It was about one
of the other victims.

184
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:41,500
They said when
she finally woke up,

185
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:43,291
she had no movement
in her right leg.

186
00:09:44,708 --> 00:09:47,541
You don't think maybe she hurt
it running from the kidnapper?

187
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:49,166
[THEO]
I'm looking into it now,

188
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:51,666
but there appears to be
a lot more to this.

189
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:52,958
[KYOICHI]
What do you mean?

190
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:54,291
[THEO]
Well, I'm pretty sure

191
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,500
she went missing in Hokkaido.

192
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:58,291
[KYOICHI]
I see.

193
00:09:58,375 --> 00:10:01,416
[THEO] Even without that theory,
we need to look into it more.

194
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,000
And we need the police
to weigh in on it as well.

195
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,416
[KYOICHI]
Why the police?

196
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,000
[THEO] Because cops
have access to information

197
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:08,625
we may not, obviously.

198
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,583
Stop by the office first.

199
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:12,875
I want to show you
what I've got.

200
00:10:12,958 --> 00:10:14,916
Be right there.

201
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,000
[bus doors hissing open]

202
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:19,750
You okay?

203
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:21,416
[KYOICHI]
Hmm? Yeah.

204
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:40,416
[sighs]

205
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:43,791
It's the only explanation.

206
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:46,791
Isn't it, sis?

207
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:14,666
So, what do you want
to talk about?

208
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,583
First of all,
take a look at this.

209
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:19,750
Go to the red bookmark.

210
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:23,791
Huh?

211
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:25,833
That's her.
The girl from yesterday.

212
00:11:25,916 --> 00:11:27,708
[KYOICHI] I've been following
this missing persons case

213
00:11:27,791 --> 00:11:29,000
for a long time.

214
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:31,458
I have a theory.

215
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:33,500
Every single one of those girls
are its victims.

216
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:35,250
There're so many.

217
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,625
[KYOICHI] Yeah.
Now go to the blue bookmark.

218
00:11:40,541 --> 00:11:42,125
[gasps]
Her name is Sakaki too!

219
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:46,875
That's right. My older sister.

220
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:52,916
Seventeen years ago, we lost
our parents very suddenly.

221
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,625
So, we were taken to live
in an orphanage.

222
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,458
-[GIRL] Kyoichi!
-Hey, sis!

223
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:02,750
Jeez, I was
so worried about you!

224
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:06,375
Sorry. It's not my fault.

225
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:10,500
Yeah, I know. But that's not how
it looked out there.

226
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:12,500
Even if you were provoked,
it becomes your fault

227
00:12:12,583 --> 00:12:13,750
if you hit first.

228
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:18,250
Let's go. The nuns
are all beside themselves.

229
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:23,291
Kyoichi.

230
00:12:32,541 --> 00:12:33,750
Shiori!

231
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:37,583
[KYOICHI panting]

232
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:39,666
[grunts]

233
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:46,666
Shiori. No.

234
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:58,083
She was kidnapped by an Another
right in front of me.

235
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:01,416
Of course, I didn't know
what it was.

236
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,708
Just that she was gone.

237
00:13:03,708 --> 00:13:05,625
That's horrible.

238
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:07,333
Ever since that day,

239
00:13:07,416 --> 00:13:10,041
I've been searching for
the Another that kidnapped her.

240
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:13,041
Where were you looking for it?
And how?

241
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,458
I went to the police first.

242
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:18,000
But that's when I learned
that the police aren't equipped

243
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:19,875
to help people
with Another-related cases.

244
00:13:22,791 --> 00:13:25,208
So, a lot happened after that.

245
00:13:25,291 --> 00:13:27,583
I needed money, badly,
so I became a host.

246
00:13:27,666 --> 00:13:29,708
That's when I first met Reiji.

247
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:34,000
When he told me
about this job, I saw it

248
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:37,000
as an opportunity
to gain access to more Anothers

249
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:39,375
and hopefully find out
what happened to my sister.

250
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:43,041
This case proves that
my instincts were spot-on.

251
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:46,958
-What do you mean by that?
-[KYOICHI] The black sand.

252
00:13:48,125 --> 00:13:49,750
Like what Shiba told us about?

253
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:51,416
Exactly.

254
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:54,291
The beast who kidnapped the
girls we found in Toyama Park

255
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,750
and the one who took
my sister are the same.

256
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:58,541
Or at least
the same kind of Another.

257
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,375
Also, do you remember
what Coyote said?

258
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:03,916
About there being
a nasty demon

259
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,833
who goes around
collecting young girls?

260
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:08,333
Yeah, I do.

261
00:14:08,416 --> 00:14:10,458
I want to know
if that's who I'm looking for.

262
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:11,958
Will you help me
talk to him?

263
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:14,333
I have some difficult questions
I'd like to ask him.

264
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:16,625
Please?

265
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,125
[PANDORA]
Loss.

266
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:24,583
The man you were with carries

267
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,458
a tremendous amount
of grief and heartbreak,

268
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:28,166
and those feelings
triggered the device.

269
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,708
[ARATA]
That's what Pandora meant.

270
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,333
His sister is his great loss.

271
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,416
Wait. When you say
"talk" to him,

272
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:36,041
do you mean "negotiate"?

273
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,416
You're the one who said
that Anothers

274
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,708
don't think the way we do.

275
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,791
They don't care what's logical.

276
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:43,416
[KYOICHI sighs]

277
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:45,708
You're right, but don't worry.

278
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:48,125
I won't try
to negotiate with him.

279
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:51,583
-[ARATA] Still...
-[KYOICHI] I'm begging you.

280
00:14:51,666 --> 00:14:54,125
I just want to hear
what he has to say.

281
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:55,708
If he knows
what happened to her.

282
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:57,750
Please don't be upset, Kyoichi.

283
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:00,083
[KYOICHI]
Help me.

284
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:02,625
♪

285
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:06,333
Okay, sure.

286
00:15:06,416 --> 00:15:08,291
I'll talk to Kohaku
when I get home.

287
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,625
I owe you one.
Thank you.

288
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:15,666
One more thing, this isn't
necessarily work related,

289
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:18,583
so there's no need
to mention it to Theo.

290
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:20,375
What? Why?

291
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,291
He's having to cover for Reiji,
so I don't want

292
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:24,125
to create
additional stress.

293
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:26,666
When the time's right,
I'll fill him in.

294
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:30,916
I won't mention it.

295
00:15:36,958 --> 00:15:38,458
Hey, Kyoichi?

296
00:15:38,541 --> 00:15:39,791
[KYOICHI]
What's up?

297
00:15:39,875 --> 00:15:41,416
She might still be alive,
you know.

298
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:44,541
Who are you
talking about?

299
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:47,291
Well, based on everything
that's happened,

300
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:50,166
your sister could
still be around.

301
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,541
Explain.

302
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:53,291
Look at Shiba.

303
00:15:53,375 --> 00:15:55,291
She was born in 1965

304
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,333
and came back
after all those years.

305
00:15:57,416 --> 00:15:58,958
Why couldn't your sister
be somewhere?

306
00:16:01,458 --> 00:16:04,958
I don't know.
I guess she could.

307
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:10,916
You're absolutely right.

308
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,583
Thank you. Seriously.

309
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:18,083
♪

310
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:37,208
What the hell? Hey, Arata!

311
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:38,750
Yeah? What's up?

312
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,208
[THEO] You're missing
some details in your paperwork.

313
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,333
You've been getting sloppy
this last week.

314
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:45,208
I... I'm so sorry.

315
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:46,541
Are you?

316
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:48,916
It's starting
to feel like a prank.

317
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,208
Are you not feeling well?

318
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:52,916
Um... no, that isn't it.

319
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:57,250
[sighs]

320
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:59,833
[KYOICHI] Maybe you just need
a little fresh air, rookie.

321
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:02,875
Hey, Theo, can I take him
on patrol with me?

322
00:17:02,958 --> 00:17:05,458
Hmm? Oh.
I guess it is that time.

323
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:09,083
Yeah, might as well.
He's just in the way here.

324
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,666
Okay. Let's go.

325
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:11,791
Right.

326
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:17,166
Yeah, those two are
definitely hiding something.

327
00:17:19,166 --> 00:17:21,791
[ARATA] I didn't see Kohaku
yesterday, either.

328
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:23,958
I have no idea
where he could be.

329
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,458
It's all right.

330
00:17:25,541 --> 00:17:27,791
I've already waited 17 years.

331
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:29,291
I'm in no rush.

332
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,791
What's wrong?

333
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:35,875
Um, it's just

334
00:17:35,958 --> 00:17:38,083
I think we should tell Theo
what's going on.

335
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,750
I'm sorry.

336
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:45,750
I realize I'm being selfish
about this whole thing.

337
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:48,583
I shouldn't have involved you
in my personal matters.

338
00:17:48,666 --> 00:17:50,875
That's why I don't want
to drag anyone else in.

339
00:17:50,958 --> 00:17:52,625
But I...

340
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:53,916
[KYOICHI]
It'll be okay.

341
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,375
There's nothing to worry about.

342
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:03,458
♪

343
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:11,666
[people chattering]

344
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,750
Sorry I'm late!

345
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:16,166
You're fine.
I just got here!

346
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:18,875
-Okay? What?
-I don't know.

347
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:20,333
I was just thinking we sound

348
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:22,000
like something out of
a dumb comic.

349
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:23,916
I didn't think people
really talked like that,

350
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,416
but I guess they do.

351
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,458
[chuckles]
Jeez, but you're right,

352
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:28,791
we didn't even sound like us.

353
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:31,166
Yep, totally awkward.

354
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:33,666
And this isn't going
to interfere with work?

355
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:36,000
Yeah, I've got plenty of time
to check out the festival.

356
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:37,708
I've just got to leave by 6:30.

357
00:18:37,791 --> 00:18:42,250
♪

358
00:18:46,791 --> 00:18:49,625
[groans]
I'm getting kinda thirsty.

359
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:53,875
What would you like? On me.

360
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:55,833
Anything not carbonated.

361
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:57,000
You got it!

362
00:18:59,291 --> 00:19:00,625
Thank you, sir

363
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:03,000
[IZUMI giggles]

364
00:19:14,416 --> 00:19:15,583
Izumi, no!

365
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:18,416
[panting]

366
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,208
-[vase shatters]
-[gasps]

367
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:26,416
That's just great.

368
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,000
He's showing up late
for work now.

369
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:31,166
Everyone runs late
sometimes, Theo.

370
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,166
We don't have any emergencies.

371
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:34,458
He'll be here soon.

372
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:35,500
[grunts]
Hey!

373
00:19:35,583 --> 00:19:37,083
Yes, dear?

374
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:38,875
[THEO]
What's going on with you two?

375
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:40,750
What are you talking about?
Explain.

376
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:42,583
You think I can't tell?

377
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:44,500
I've known you
for a very long time.

378
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,916
What are you hiding?

379
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:50,625
Look, it's none of my business
what you guys do

380
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,125
when you're off the clock.

381
00:19:52,208 --> 00:19:54,666
But, come on, that kid
just got hired on with us.

382
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:56,708
And whatever it is,
it's affecting his work.

383
00:19:56,791 --> 00:19:59,500
-That's not--
-[cell phone buzzing]

384
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:03,916
[KYOICHI]
Arata?

385
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,333
Hey, Arata, what's going on?

386
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:08,000
-[ARATA on phone] They took her.
-Took who?

387
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:10,875
[ARATA] Izumi.
One of my oldest friends.

388
00:20:10,958 --> 00:20:13,458
She was kidnapped by an Another
right in front of me.

389
00:20:13,541 --> 00:20:14,625
[BOTH gasp]

390
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:15,875
[ARATA]
I think it's the same one

391
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,375
you were talking about,

392
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:19,000
the one who took your sister.

393
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:21,375
There was all this black sand.
It came out of nowhere!

394
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:24,625
[THEO]
Black sand?

395
00:20:24,708 --> 00:20:28,000
You mean like in Toyama Park?

396
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:29,791
That has nothing to do
with your sister.

397
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:32,916
Or does it? Kyoichi?

398
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,625
What's going on, Kyoichi?

399
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,916
♪

400
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,125
[KYOICHI]
During the Toyama Park incident,

401
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:42,916
it occurred to me
that Coyote might have had

402
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,458
some information
about my sister.

403
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,416
So I asked Arata
if he would help me talk to him.

404
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,958
[THEO grunts]

405
00:20:51,958 --> 00:20:54,000
What do you mean
you wanted to talk to him?

406
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:56,208
You mean negotiate with him?

407
00:20:56,291 --> 00:20:58,666
After lecturing the rookie
on how dangerous that is?

408
00:21:02,708 --> 00:21:04,583
Arata, I'm on the way.

409
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,666
Stay exactly where you are.
Got that?

410
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:08,916
[ARATA]
Yeah.

411
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:12,291
Damn it! Why Izumi?

412
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:15,250
And what are the odds?
It wasn't random.

413
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:17,500
Kohaku! Where are you?

414
00:21:17,583 --> 00:21:20,083
I know you're here! Come out!

415
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:21,208
[gasps]

416
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:26,333
♪

417
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:27,958
You rang?

418
00:23:01,208 --> 00:23:02,750
I like that look on your face.

419
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:04,041
I can't say I've ever seen it

420
00:23:04,125 --> 00:23:05,583
in the entire time
I've known you.

421
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:06,875
You bastard!

422
00:23:06,958 --> 00:23:08,416
[COYOTE]
Why me?

423
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:10,208
I'm not the one
you should be upset with

424
00:23:10,291 --> 00:23:11,875
if you really think about it.

425
00:23:12,916 --> 00:23:15,541
I mean, there's a demon
whose whole existence revolves

426
00:23:15,625 --> 00:23:17,375
around collecting young girls.

427
00:23:17,458 --> 00:23:19,625
He's the one who helped me
with the Kyoshi ritual,

428
00:23:19,708 --> 00:23:20,833
and who took your friend.

429
00:23:20,916 --> 00:23:22,500
Then tell me where she is?

430
00:23:22,583 --> 00:23:24,166
Where did he take her?

431
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:29,666
A place you'll never be able
to reach, unfortunately.

432
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:32,416
What do you mean, "reach?"
Where is it?

433
00:23:33,416 --> 00:23:34,416
[COYOTE]
Hmm?

434
00:23:35,875 --> 00:23:37,750
[roaring, snarling]

435
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:39,875
[COYOTE]
It's called, "Hell."

